abstract = {The smart-city concept is expected to be realized in the near future, which affects the development of novel mobile networks such as 5G. In order to provide access to larger bandwidths and higher frequencies, the 5G network increases the complexity of the RF front-end components. Designers have to satisfy tighter specifications for realizing components such as filters, antennas, phase shifters, power amplifiers and switches. In order to optimize the energy consumption in the RF front-end module, nonvolatile components could be used as memristors. Memristors are potential candidates to enable reconfigurability and tunability of RF and microwave components. In this chapter, we present possible memristor applications in the design of RF/microwave components such as reconfigurable multi-band filters and digital phase shifters. The main idea is to replace traditional RF/microwave switches with memristors in order to reduce power consumption. For microwave filter design, memristors could be used to realize reconfigurability of the multi-band bandpass planar filters.}
